element.name: Resource
element.documentation: A resource represents an asset owned or controlled by an individual or organization.

element.name: Capability
element.documentation: A capability represents an ability that an active structure element, such as an organization, person, or system, possesses.

element.name: Course Of Action
element.documentation: A course of action is an approach or plan for configuring some capabilities and resources of the enterprise, undertaken to achieve a goal.

element.name: Product
element.documentation: A product represents a coherent collection of services and/or passive structure elements, accompanied by a contract/set of agreements, which is offered as a whole to (internal or external) customers.

element.name: Business Actor
element.documentation: A business actor is a business entity that is capable of performing behavior

element.name: Business Role
element.documentation: A business role is the responsibility for performing specific behavior, to which an actor can be assigned, or the part an actor plays in a particular action or event

element.name: Business Collaboration
element.documentation: A business collaboration is an aggregate of two or more business internal active structure elements that work together to perform collective behavior

element.name: Business Interface
element.documentation: A business interface is a point of access where a business service is made available to the environment.

element.name: Business Process
element.documentation: A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome such as a defined set of products or business services.

element.name: Business Function
element.documentation: A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria (typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization, but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

element.name: Business Interaction
element.documentation: A business interaction is a unit of collective business behavior performed by (a collaboration of) two or more business roles

element.name: Business Service
element.documentation: A business service represents an explicitly defined exposed business behavior

element.name: Business Event
element.documentation: A business event is a business behavior element that denotes an organizational state change. It may originate from and be resolved inside or outside the organization

element.name: Business Object
element.documentation: A business object represents a concept used within a particular business domain

element.name: Contract
element.documentation: A contract represents a formal or informal specification of an agreement between a provider and a consumer that specifies the rights and obligations associated with a product and establishes functional and non-functional parameters for interaction

element.name: Representation
element.documentation: A representation represents a perceptible form of the information carried by a business object

element.name: Business Function (copy)
element.documentation: A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria (typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization, but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

element.name: Business Function
element.documentation: A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria (typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization, but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

element.name: Business Process
element.documentation: A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome such as a defined set of products or business services.

element.name: Business Process (copy)
element.documentation: A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome such as a defined set of products or business services.

element.name: Application Component
element.documentation: An application component represents an encapsulation of application functionality aligned to implementation structure, which is modular and replaceable. It encapsulates its behavior and data, exposes services, and makes them available through interfaces.

element.name: Application Collaboration
element.documentation: An application collaboration represents an aggregate of two or more application components that work together to perform collective application behavior.

element.name: Application Interface
element.documentation: An application interface represents a point of access where application services are made available to a user, another application component, or a node.

element.name: Application Interaction
element.documentation: An application interaction represents a unit of collective application behavior performed by (a collaboration of) two or more application components.

element.name: Application Service
element.documentation: An application service represents an explicitly defined exposed application behavior

element.name: Application Event
element.documentation: An application event is an application behavior element that denotes a state change

element.name: Data Object
element.documentation: A data object represents data structured for automated processing

element.name: Application Function
element.documentation: An application function represents automated behavior that can be performed by an application component

element.name: Application Process
element.documentation: An application process represents a sequence of application behaviors that achieves a specific outcome.

element.name: Application Process (copy)
element.documentation: An application process represents a sequence of application behaviors that achieves a specific outcome.

element.name: Node
element.documentation: A node represents a computational or physical resource that hosts, manipulates, or interacts with other computational or physical resources.

element.name: Device
element.documentation: A device is a physical IT resource upon which system software and artifacts may be stored or deployed for execution.

element.name: System Software
element.documentation: System software represents software that provides or contributes to an environment for storing, executing, and using software or data deployed within it.

element.name: Technology Collaboration
element.documentation: A technology collaboration represents an aggregate of two or more nodes that work together to perform collective technology behavior.

element.name: Path
element.documentation: A path represents a link between two or more nodes, through which these nodes can exchange data or material.

element.name: Communication Network
element.documentation: A communication network represents a set of structures and behaviors that connects computer systems or other electronic devices for transmission, routing, and reception of data or data-based communications such as voice and video.

element.name: Technology Interface
element.documentation: A technology interface represents a point of access where technology services offered by a node can be accessed.

element.name: Technology Interaction
element.documentation: A technology interaction represents a unit of collective technology behavior performed by (a collaboration of) two or more nodes.

element.name: Technology Service
element.documentation: A technology service represents an explicitly defined exposed technology behavior.

element.name: Technology Event
element.documentation: A technology event is a technology behavior element that denotes a state change.

element.name: Artifact
element.documentation: An artifact represents a piece of data that is used or produced in a software development process, or by deployment and operation of an IT system. (A technology object represents a passive element that is used or produced by technology behavior.)

element.name: Equipment
element.documentation: Equipment represents one or more physical machines, tools, or instruments that can create, use, store, move, or transform materials.

element.name: Facility
element.documentation: A facility represents a physical structure or environment

element.name: Distribution Network
element.documentation: A distribution network represents a physical network used to transport materials or energy

element.name: Material
element.documentation: Material represents tangible physical matter or physical elements

element.name: Technology Function
element.documentation: A technology function represents a collection of technology behavior that can be performed by a node.

element.name: Technology Process
element.documentation: A technology process represents a sequence of technology behaviors that achieves a specific outcome.

element.name: Technology Process (copy)
element.documentation: A technology process represents a sequence of technology behaviors that achieves a specific outcome.

element.name: Stakeholder
element.documentation: A stakeholder is the role of an individual, team, or organization (or classes thereof) that represents their interests in the outcome of the architecture.

element.name: Driver
element.documentation: A driver represents an external or internal condition that motivates an organization to define its goals and implement the changes necessary to achieve them.

element.name: Assessment
element.documentation: An assessment represents the result of an analysis of the state of affairs of the enterprise with respect to some driver.

element.name: Goal
element.documentation: A goal represents a high-level statement of intent, direction, or desired end state for an organization and its stakeholders.

element.name: Outcome
element.documentation: An outcome represents an end result that has been achieved

element.name: Principle
element.documentation: A principle represents a qualitative statement of intent that should be met by the architecture

element.name: Requirement
element.documentation: A requirement represents a statement of need that must be met by the architecture.

element.name: Constraint
element.documentation: A constraint represents a factor that prevents or obstructs the realization of goals.

element.name: Meaning
element.documentation: Meaning represents the knowledge or expertise present in, or the interpretation given to, a core element in a particular context.

element.name: Value
element.documentation: Value represents the relative worth, utility, or importance of a core element or an outcome.

element.name: Work Package
element.documentation: A work package represents a series of actions identified and designed to achieve specific results within specified time and resource constraints.

element.name: Implementation Event
element.documentation: An implementation event is a behavior element that denotes a state change related to implementation or migration

element.name: Deliverable
element.documentation: A deliverable represents a precisely-defined outcome of a work package

element.name: Plateau
element.documentation: A plateau represents a relatively stable state of the architecture that exists during a limited period of time.

element.name: Gap
element.documentation: A gap represents a statement of difference between two plateaus

element.name: Plateau
element.documentation: A plateau represents a relatively stable state of the architecture that exists during a limited period of time.

element.name: strategic
element.documentation: Strategic Architecture provides an organizing framework for operational and change activity and allows for direction setting at an executive level.

element.name: segment
element.documentation: Segment Architecture provides an organizing framework for operational and change activity and allows for direction setting and the development of effective architecture roadmaps at a program or portfolio level.

element.name: capability
element.documentation: Capability Architecture provides an organizing framework for change activity and the development of effective architecture roadmaps realizing capability increments. o current capability, o target capability, and o capability increments (work packages and projects to be grouped within managed portfolios and programs)
